Example: Rewrite 365{\displaystyle {\frac {36}{5}}} as a mixed number. How many times does 5 fit evenly into 36? 5 x 7 = 35, so the whole number portion is 7. What's left over? The whole number portion is equivalent to 355{\displaystyle {\frac {35}{5}}}, so solve 365{\displaystyle {\frac {36}{5}}} - 355{\displaystyle {\frac {35}{5}}} = 15{\displaystyle {\frac {1}{5}}}

